FBIS3-6230 "dreas050_a_94016" FBIS-EAS-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hosokawa, Norwegian Parliamentary Leader Meet OW1403095394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0932 GMT 14 Mar 94 OW1403095394 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, March 14 KYODO -- Norwegian parliamentary leader Kristi Kolle Grondahl Monday [14 March] met Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa for an exchange of greetings and a brief discussion of Russia's disposal of radioactive waste into the Sea of Japan. Grondahl, president of the 165-member Storting, remarked that Norway faces a similar problem with Russian nuclear dumping near its own borders, government officials said. She said Prime Minister Gro Harlem Brundtland, who canceled plans to visit Japan in January because of a cold, hopes to visit in the near future to discuss the problem. Hosokawa said Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata plans to raise the issue when he visits Russia this month. Grondahl is visiting Japan at the invitation of the House of Councillors.
